# Recall — project rules

Read `CLAUDE.md` at repo root for full architecture.

## Golden rules

1. Never put provider API keys in the mobile app — backend `.env` only.
2. Use model aliases in app code: `free-chat`, `smart-chat`, `title-model`, `memory-model`. Provider mapping only in `apps/api/app/gateways/litellm_gateway.py`.
3. Never send full chat history to the model — memory + recent window (~10–20 messages) only.
4. Topic generation and memory extraction are best-effort background jobs — must never block streaming.
5. No arbitrary code execution — render/highlight code only. The sole exception: HTML/CSS/JS preview in a sandboxed WebView (and chart/diagram rendering). Never run Python/shell/etc., and never run code outside that isolated WebView. The preview WebView needs a dev build (not Expo Go).
6. Validate all LLM structured outputs with Pydantic before DB writes.

## Layering (backend)

`routers/` → `services/` → `gateways/` + `repositories/`. No business logic in routers.

New chat-loop code belongs in `apps/api/app/services/chat/`.

## Mobile

- All HTTP/WebSocket via `apps/mobile/lib/api.ts`
- Tokens in `expo-secure-store` only
- Screens stay dumb; logic in hooks (`useChat`, auth context)

## In scope (current)

Chat + memory, todos, proactive suggestions, full-text search, i18n, and rich rendering (markdown, math, charts, sandboxed HTML/JS preview).

## v1 non-goals

No tools/agents, no execution of non-web code (Python/shell/etc.) or execution outside the sandboxed preview WebView, no multi-user.

A **web client sharing this same API** is planned for a later version — keep `lib/api.ts` the single network boundary and rich-block rendering swappable so the app stays portable.
